author: John Kennedy
title: Court rejects House, Senate redistricting plans
text:
A Leon County judge dealt a blow Friday to the Republican-led House and Senate, rejecting their plans for drawing congressional boundaries and siding with the approach taken by a voters’ coalition.
Circuit Judge Terry Lewis said the proposal by the League of Women Voters and Common Cause “hands down” did a better job of keeping cities and counties together.
